privacy_police_second_section_descriptio:
2.1. The application collects the following data: 

 Registration data: name, email, telephone (when voluntarily provided by the user); 
 Usage data: records of navigation in the application and interactions with features; 
 Media data: images and videos uploaded by the user for the purpose of recording occurrences.

privacy_police_third_section_description:
The data collected is used to: 
 Allow the registration and management of incidents; 
 Forward information to competent authorities; 
 Improve the user experience and the security of the platform; 
 Comply with legal and regulatory obligations.

privacy_police_fourth_section_descriptio:
The data may be shared: 
 With public bodies and private companies for the purposes of analyzing and resolving incidents; 
 When there is a legal obligation or court order; 
 With strategic partners to improve the application, respecting data protection standards.

privacy_police_sixth_section_description:
Users have the right to: 
 Request access to their personal data; 
 Request the correction or deletion of information; 
 Revoke consents granted. Requests should be sent to: {count}.

use_terms_third_section_description:
3.1. The user is responsible for the veracity, integrity and legality of the information entered in the application. 

 3.2. It is expressly forbidden to send: 
 False, defamatory, slanderous content or content that violates the honor of third parties; 
 Images and videos that expose people without consent or that violate privacy rights; 
 Confidential data or data protected by specific legislation without express authorization; 
 Content that violates any applicable legislation. 

 3.3. The Detect and Solve administration reserves the right to remove any content that does not comply with these terms, and may also suspend or delete user accounts that violate the rules described herein. 

 3.4. The application may share the information entered with competent authorities whenever necessary to fulfill its purpose.
